<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-7535] KafkaConsumer doesn&apos;t report records-lag if isolation.level is read_committed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-7535</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Starting from 2.0.0, &lt;tt&gt;KafkaConsumer&lt;/tt&gt; doesn&apos;t report &lt;tt&gt;records-lag&lt;/tt&gt; if &lt;tt&gt;isolation.level&lt;/tt&gt; is &lt;tt&gt;read_committed&lt;/tt&gt;. The last version, where it works is &lt;tt&gt;1.1.1&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The issue can be easily reproduced in &lt;tt&gt;kafka.api.PlaintextConsumerTest&lt;/tt&gt; by adding &lt;tt&gt;consumerConfig.setProperty(&quot;isolation.level&quot;, &quot;read_committed&quot;)&lt;/tt&gt; witin related tests:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;testPerPartitionLagMetricsCleanUpWithAssign&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;testPerPartitionLagMetricsCleanUpWithSubscribe&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;testPerPartitionLagWithMaxPollRecords&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
